reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great in a Mazda RX-8
reviews.reviewText: Given my previous experience using this on an aircraft with a Lycoming O-360, and my battery finally failing in my RX8 Mazda, I decided to give it a try. Given that lead acid battery prices have gotten ridiculous as of late, specifically a group 35 for my car was 219 for a cheap one, over 300 for a yellowtop, both rated at 640cca. Then we have the weight savings! This battery is 6.6lbs and the AGM Lead one is almost 44.OK, on to the fitment. This battery is both shorter and narrower than the OEM one, however, the foam that was in the packaging almost filled the gaps needed. I took off the traditional terminals, which was 1 nut, and attached the leads directly to the battery. In my case I had to use different hardware on the positive terminal as I had to put a spacer under, so needed a longer bolt.The car fired right to life, even without charging. After it got a bit of charge to it, the starter turns over really fast now.For the price, this is a tremendous value.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great battery for BMW R1200
reviews.reviewText: I used this in a 1998 R1200C since the battery pocket is unusual and the battery available was much more money than this one.It has worked well since installation.Has flexible installation options for the battery post.I had to exchange the first one because I did not pay attention to how the plus & minus posts were oriented. My fault but was easy exchange.Prior battery had 190 CCA listed on the case. This one is more than double that.It has reliably started the big 1200 cc twin since I put it in.Is now winter in Colorado and the bike is outdoors on a battery tender special to LiFPo batteries.It has been below zero twice and it still works just fine.This battery was about 1/3 weight of AGM unit I removed from the bike.I will come back to this company for another battery when needed for lawn tractor and other Harley Road King.I am happy with this battery

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good battery close fit
reviews.reviewText: It was delivered on time the next day. It was the exact same size as my original battery. A 2017 ultra limited HD. The terminal holes were the correct thread for my previous bolts but the they were inset about a half inch further back. Since the battery cables were L shaped they wouldn't reach so I had to straighten out the battery cables to fit. Very satisfied with everything else.
